<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">38767178</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2025</Year><Month>11</Month><Day>12</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>01</Month><Day>27</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print-Electronic"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1478-6427</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>39</Volume><Issue>20</Issue><PubDate><Year>2025</Year><Month>Oct</Month></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Natural product research</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Nat Prod Res</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Angeliticin B, a new chromone isolated from <i>Angelica polymorpha</i> Maxim.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>5792</StartPage><EndPage>5798</EndPage><MedlinePgn>5792-5798</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1080/14786419.2024.2354860</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>A new chromone, angeliticin B (<b>1</b>) together with nine known compounds, psoralene (<b>2</b>), isoimperatorin (<b>3</b>), (<i>S</i>)-(-)-2'-methoxypeucedanin hydrate (<b>4</b>), (<i>S)</i>-(-)-oxypeucedanin (<b>5</b>), xanthotoxin (<b>6</b>), isopimpinellin (<b>7</b>), 1'-<i>O</i>-<i>&#x3b2;</i>-D-glucopyranosyl-(2'<i>S</i>, 3'<i>R</i>)-3'-hydroxymarmesin (<b>8</b>), <i>sec</i>-<i>O</i>-glucosylhamaudol (<b>9</b>) and vanillin (<b>10</b>) were isolated from the methanol extract of <i>Angelica polymorpha</i> Maxim. The structures of these compounds were elucidated through a comprehensive analysis of standard spectral data (MS, IR, and NMR). Compound <b>1</b> exhibited antioxidant activity with IC<sub>50</sub> = 198.57&#x2009;&#x3bc;M in DPPH experiment and 31.71&#x2009;&#x3bc;M in ABTS experiment. Compound <b>2</b>, <b>6</b>, <b>7</b> exhibited ABTS radical scavenging activity with IC<sub>50</sub> ranging from 105.96&#x2009;&#x3bc;M to 167.67&#x2009;&#x3bc;M. Compound <b>3</b> demonstrated a synergistic induction effect on nigericin-activated NLRP3 inflammasome in THP-1 cell by LDH release method.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Yang</LastName><ForeName>Li</ForeName><Initials>L</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Medicinal Natural Products, West China School of Pharmacy, Sichuan University, Chengdu, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Dai</LastName><ForeName>Yanlin</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Medicinal Natural Products, West China School of Pharmacy, Sichuan University, Chengdu, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Wang</LastName><ForeName>Jianzhong</ForeName><Initials>J</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Medicinal Natural Products, West China School of Pharmacy, Sichuan University, Chengdu, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Chen</LastName><ForeName>Donglin</ForeName><Initials>D</Initials><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Department of Medicinal Natural Products, West China School of Pharmacy, Sichuan University, Chengdu, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Key Laboratory of Drug Targeting and Drug Delivery System Ministry of Education, West China School of Pharmacy, Sichuan University, Chengdu, China.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author></AuthorList><Language>eng</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI="D016428">Journal Article</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList><ArticleDate DateType="Electronic"><Year>2024</Year><Month>05</Month><Day>20</Day></ArticleDate></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>England</Country><MedlineTA>Nat Prod Res</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>101167924</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>1478-6419</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><ChemicalList><Chemical><RegistryNumber>0</RegistryNumber><NameOfSubstance UI="D002867">Chromones</NameOfSubstance></Chemical><Chemical><RegistryNumber>0</RegistryNumber><NameOfSubstanc